# 
traindata[, -1] <- traindata[, -1] > 0
testdata[, -1] <- testdata[, -1] > 0

# e1071naiveBayes()
library(e1071)
## Warning: package 'e1071' was built under R version 3.6.3
bayes1 <- naiveBayes( ~ ., data = traindata)

# 
predictdata <- predict(bayes1, testdata[, -1])

library(ggplot2)
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 3.6.3
ConfusionM <- as.data.frame(table(actualclass = testdata$, predictclass = predictdata))
ggplot(ConfusionM, aes(predictclass, actualclass)) + 
  geom_tile(aes(fill = Freq), color = "white")  + 
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "orange") + 
  geom_text(aes(label=Freq), color="black") + labs(title = '')
